git config-version          [<options>] - Add    version configuration options.
git config-version --remove [<options>] - Remove version configuration options.

    -h|--help               display help

'update-version' section:

    --vp|--version-props[=FILE]  Use Version.props style files (default to './Version.props').
    --pj|--package-json[=FILE]   Use package.json style files (default to './package.json').
    --ai|--assembly-info[=FILE]  Use AssemblyInfo.cs style files (default to '*/AssemblyInfo*.cs').
    --cs|--csproj[=FILE]         Use .NET Framework C# project style files (default to '*/*.cspro').
    --rc[=FILE]                  Use C++ resource files (default to '*/*.rc').
    --custom                     Add a custom version updater template file (update-version).
    --no-edit                    Do not edit custom version updater
    --remove                     Remove specified option
    
    example:
        git config-version --vp                     # add 'update_version.version-props = ./Version.props'
        git config-version --vp --remove            # remove 'update_version.version-props' key
        git config-version --ai='./AssemblyInfo.cs' # add 'update_version.assembly-info = ./AssemblyInfo.cs'
